  <rte>
    <name>Crinkle Crags and Bowfell (Oxendale Horseshoe) </name>
	<desc>The summits of the Crinkle Crags and Bowfell have always been popular objectives for walkers in the Lake District. This route follows a circuit of rugged Oxendale to reach the summits.</desc>
	<author>Copyright Walking Britain</author>
	<url>www.walkingbritain.co.uk/walk-1739-description</url>
